tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE SurveyData (
    participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    income DECIMAL(10,2),
    education_level VARCHAR(50),
    survey_response TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Survey_Responses (
  response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  question_id INT, 
  response_text VARCHAR,
  response_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Demographic_Information (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR,
  education_level VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE Variable_Correlations (
  correlation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  variable1_id INT,
  variable2_id INT,
  correlation_coefficient FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE Survey_Response_Demographics (
  response_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (response_id) REFERENCES Survey_Responses(response_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Demographic_Information(user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE SurveyResponses (id INT PRIMARY KEY, response TEXT, participant_id INT, question_id INT) 

CREATE TABLE DemographicInfo (id INT PRIMARY KEY, participant_id INT, age INT, gender TEXT) 

CREATE TABLE Questions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, question_text TEXT, category TEXT) 

CREATE TABLE Participants (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, email TEXT) 

CREATE TABLE CorrelationData (id INT PRIMARY KEY, question_id INT, participant_id INT, response_value INT)
